arStrings.szText: The door bears an image of a snake. Her eyes are missing—perhaps returning them here is the key to opening the way.
To self upon seeing a great door leading into the temple. It has the image of a snake, but the eyes are missing.
La représentation d’un serpent orne la porte. Ses yeux ont disparu ; leur restitution est peut-être la clé pour ouvrir le passage.
